Anacron
	Used when system is not running continuously
	Executes missed cron jobs after system starts
  
We perform anacron for:
       Daily System Backup
       Weekly Log File Cleaning
       Monthly Reports Generation
       Software  Updates
       Databases Maintenance
   
Cron jobs fail if the system is OFF.
Anacron runs missed jobs automatically when system starts.

Configuration file:

/etc/anacrontab

Example entry

1   5   backup-job   /home/user/backup.sh
1   1   test-job echo"ANACRON JOB RUN at $(date)" >> /tmp/demo.log
